               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner. I was in the habit of going to that pawnbroker's, and I was stopped there, when I was taken into custody. Witness. I detained her on the 9th of November, because Mrs. Benham had given us information. I sent for her, but she did not come for some time, and I let the prisoner go - she said she had bought the curtain.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I told the gentleman I had bought the curtain of a woman at the corner of Peter-street - he asked if I could describe the woman, and if she had a cut in her finger - I said Yes.</p>
